verbose_text: Moreover, CsPDAT1-C was mainly expressed in leaf and flower tissues (XREF_FIG A), whereas CsPDAT2-A and CsPDAT2-B were preferentially expressed in stem and root tissues, respectively (XREF_FIG B), suggesting that CsPDAT1-C, CsPDAT2-A and CsPDAT2-B may have some other, yet unknown, physiological functions in addition to TAG synthesis in each of these non seed tissues of camelina.
evidence: CsPDAT2-A and CsPDAT2-B were preferentially expressed
